---
title: `$shield::state()`
description: Get shield state data.
...

~~~ .php.xmp
Shield::state($id, $key = null, $fail = false);
~~~

**Example:**

Return the stored shield states if any, otherwise, return `$fail`:

~~~ .php
$state = Shield::state('document');
~~~

> **Note:** If `$key` is array, then it will going to be the alternate values of the `$state` output if some data are not available; `$fail` data value will be ignored:
>
> ~~~ .php
> $state = Shield::state('document', [
>     'chunk' => 5 // add `chunk` property to `$state` if missing
> ]);
> ~~~